  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2015-10-01", 
    "text": "Expanding Opportunities for Recovery Act of 2015\n\nThis bill requires the Center for Substance Abuse Treatment in the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration to award grants to states to expand access to clinically appropriate services for opioid abuse or addiction. States must use these grants to provide up to 60 consecutive days of services to individuals who otherwise would not have access to substance abuse services."
